# /etc/fw_env.config — tells libubootenv (fw_printenv/fw_setenv, used by the
# wendyos-update ubootenv connector) where the U-Boot environment lives.
#
# WendyOS RPi (wendy OTA stack) stores it as uboot.env on the FAT boot
# partition (CONFIG_ENV_IS_IN_FAT in stock meta-raspberrypi U-Boot), which the
# rootfs mounts at /boot (rpi-wendy-fstab). Single (non-redundant) file-backed
# env; libubootenv edits the file in place.
#
# The env size MUST equal U-Boot's CONFIG_ENV_SIZE for RPi — verify against the
# u-boot defconfig; a mismatch corrupts the env on the first fw_setenv.
#
# <device or file>   <offset>   <env size>
/boot/uboot.env      0x0000     0x4000
